    <stitle>CF 500, CF 600 Brakes - Front Disc Brake - Front Disc Brake Description and Operation</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Front Disc Brake Description and Operation</title>
        <para>The front disc brake caliper:</para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>bolts to the front disc brake caliper anchor plate, which bolts to the front wheel spindle.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>is a dual piston, pin slider design.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>has a fluid inlet at the center of the caliper housing.</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <para>The front disc brake discs:</para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>are of a ventilated full-cast design, with non-directional cooling fins.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>are mounted to the front wheel spindle.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>are serviced with the disc brake caliper and front disc brake caliper anchor plate removed.</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <para>The front brake disc shield:</para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>is bolted to the brake caliper anchor plate.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>protects the front wheel bearings and inboard surface of the front disc brake rotor.</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <para>The brake pads:</para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>are housed in the front disc brake caliper anchor plate.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>are of a non-asbestos, semi-metallic composition.</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
    </svcproc>
